Common.Highlight.Common.Text: Seven storey building with 18 car spaces

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
CBRE, as the exclusive sales agent, is pleased to present 111-117 Devonshire Street, Surry Hills to the market. This outstanding freehold building is situated just a moment’s walk from Central Station, hugging the boundary between Sydney CBD and the thriving Surry Hills. Capitalising on Sydney’s strong office market, the building is fully leased to seven whole floor tenants with mix use zoning and offers significant rental reversion and conversion opportunity. An exclusive opportunity within Sydney’s City Fringe, 111-117 Devonshire Street is one of the most premier office investments in the Sydney metropolitan market in recent times.

111-117 Devonshire Street benefits from the following key attributes: 

- Seven storey freehold office building with NLA of 2,085sqm*
- Basement car parking for 18 secure spaces
- WALE (income): 1.67 years*, WALE (area): 1.66 years* 
- Significant rental reversion opportunity 
- B4 Mixed Use Zoning lending itself to hotel or residential conversion
- Prime location between Surry Hills and Sydney CBD 
- 220m* to Central Station 
- Located on the doorstep of the Light Rail with the Surry Hills Light Rail Stop just 300m* away
- 4-star NABERS Energy rating

111-117 Devonshire Street, Surry Hills will be sold by way of public auction on Tuesday, 16 October 2018 at 10:30am at AuctionWORKS.

*Approximate

For more information, please contact the exclusive selling agents.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
CBRE, as the exclusive selling agent, is pleased to
present 111-115 Albion Street Surry Hills. The property is a historic three storey brick office building located within the captivating and vibrant city fringe suburb of Surry Hills. 

111-115 Albion Street benefits from the
following key attributes:

- First time offered to the market in 30 years
- Land area: 354sqm*
- NLA: 970sqm*
- Formally the old Chefs Warehouse
- Surry Hills investment or occupy opportunity
- New refurbishment plan designed by award winning architects, ACME
- Three street frontages providing strong natural light and ventilation
- Direct beneficiary of the future Sydney Metro, Light Rail and central Station upgrade projects

The property will be offered for sale via Expression of Interest 
closing on Wednesday, 3 July 2019 at 4:00pm.

For further information, please contact the exclusive CBRE selling agents.

Common.Highlight.Common.Text: Prime location along main dining strip

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
CBRE, as the exclusive sales agent, is pleased to present, Shop 13, 329-333 Crown Street, Surry Hills.

The property is a secure retail investment located in the heart of Surry Hills, home to some of Sydney’s greatest cafes, bars, restaurants and nightlife. 329-333 Crown Street is tenanted by award-winning Vietnamese restaurant, Xage and offers unrivalled access to the city’s best amenity with bus services on its doorstep and only a short walk to both Central Station and the future light rail network; providing direct access to Sydney CBD.

329-333 Crown Street benefits from the below key attributes:

- Prime location along Surry Hills’ main dining and retail strip. 
- Short walk to Central Station, Light Rail and Sydney CBD
- Retail suite with a total strata area of 175sqm*
- Award-winning tenant on a long-term lease to 2024 with 5 year option

Shop 13, 329-333 Crown Street will be sold via public auction on Tuesday, 10th March 2020 at 10.30am at AuctionWORKS.

*approximate

CBRE as the exclusive sales agent is pleased to present 24 Wentworth Avenue, Surry Hills. First time offered in 50 years, the property is a immaculately maintained commercial freehold building with a NLA of 428sqm* across four storeys. Situated on the edge of Sydney CBD, the property is moments from ample of amenities, shops and restaurants. 
  
The property benefit from the following key attributes:
•	Premium location in close proximity to Sydney CBD amenities, shops, & restaurant
•	Significant value add opportunity 
•	Potential to capitalise on further refurbishment, conversion to creative office & addition of another storey through favourable planning controls (STCA)
•	Secure & flexible investment with favourable B4 Mixed Use zoning – suitable for commercial, retail and residential 
•	NLA of 428sqm* across four storeys
•	Immaculately maintained building with an abundance of natural light and cross-ventilation. 

24 Wentworth Avenue, Surry Hills will be sold via expressions of interest closing on Wednesday, 13 November 2019 at 4pm.

For more information or to request access to the due diligence room, please contact the exclusive selling agents.

Common.Highlight.Common.Text: Ideal for owner occupiers and investors

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
CBRE is pleased to present 1-5 Flinders Street, Surry Hills, a landmark building in the heart of one of Sydney’s most renowned locations, Taylor Square.

Commanding an unrivaled exposure to Taylor Square, the recognisable freehold building is a rare offering in a coveted and tightly held city fringe location.

1-5 Flinders Street, Surry Hills benefits from the following key attributes:
- Landmark Sydney building
- Prime Taylor Square location in the heart of Oxford Street
- Internal area of 922.79sqm*
- Vacant possession property ready for incoming tenant refurbishment
- Island site frontages to Bourke Street, Flinders Street, Patterson Lane and the pedestrian traffic of Taylor Square
- B2 Local Centre zoning allowing for a variety of permissible uses

The property will be offered for sale via Expression of Interest closing on Wednesday 25 October at 4:00pm

*approximate
